data.description:
Charming brick boho bungalow in the heart of the coveted Cole neighborhood. 

This well-maintained, historic, RiNo district home offers timeless character & style combined with modern amenities. The beautiful brick structure, architectural accents, large fenced front yard & inviting covered front porch welcome you home.

The open concept main floor with original hardwood floors is light & bright. The stunning, upgraded, kitchen is a chef's delight with quartz counters, double oven & induction cooktop.  Upgraded electric system, copper plumbing and newer roof, double-paned windows.

The generous, private, fenced backyard is ideal for outdoor living with a patio, garden beds & storage shed. The rear area offers abundant parking & plenty of room to build a garage. 

This home offers highly desirable U-SU-A1 zoning for an alternative dwelling unit with great potential for additional living space, guest suite or separate rental income unit. 

Quick & easy access to everything under the sun - dining & shopping, pubs & coffee shops, gyms & yoga studios, breweries & beer gardens, vintage stores & boutiques, entertainment, Movement RiNo Climbing gym, Larimer Street, Zeppelin Station Dining hall & event center, Denver Central Market, Mission Ballroom, Cervantes’ Masterpiece Ballroom & RiNo art district. Nearby amenities include light rail, bus, schools, hospitals, parks & bike paths. Close to I-70 & I-25 & only 30 min to DIA for ultimate convenience. Premier location to enjoy city living with the privacy & comfort of a residential neighborhood.
